Description

Given an array of N integers and Q queries. In each query two integers L, R are given, you have to find the value of

(A[L] + A[L+1] + A[L+2] + ⋯ + A[R]) % (10^9 + 7)

Input Format

* The first line contains two space-separated integers N, Q where:

  * 1 ≤ N ≤ 10^6
  * 1 ≤ Q ≤ 10^6
* The next line contains N space-separated integers A1, A2, …, AN where:

  * −10^9 ≤ Ai ≤ 10^9
* The next Q lines each contain two space-separated integers L, R where:

  * 1 ≤ L ≤ R ≤ N

Output Format

For each query print the value of

(A[L] + A[L+1] + A[L+2] + ⋯ + A[R]) % (10^9 + 7)

in a new line.

Constraints

* 1 ≤ N ≤ 10^6
* 1 ≤ Q ≤ 10^6
* −10^9 ≤ Ai ≤ 10^9

Time Limit

* 4 seconds

